author: @ipvikas
text: Using 'FASTAPI' in Google colab is comparatively easy:      #step 1: import  !pip install colabcode -q !pip install fastapi -q  from colabcode import ColabCode from fastapi import FastAPI cc = ColabCode(port=12000, code=False)   app = FastAPI() #step2: instance  @app.get('/') #step4: Decorate def index():   return 'Hello World' #step3: function    cc.run_app(app=app)    #  Once it is executed and we get the .io URL, just add '/docs'  at the end of the URL i.e.  XYZ.io/docs
